# Base Standards

## Purpose
Define the minimum engineering standards for this Python AI Engineering project.

## Core Principles
- Prefer simple, working, tested code over broad abstractions.
- Work in baby steps: one small change, verify, then continue.
- Read existing code and docs before editing.
- Keep reusable logic out of notebooks and one-off scripts.
- Use English for code, comments, commit messages, technical rules, and internal specs.
- Use Spanish for learning notes in the Second Brain when appropriate.
- Do not add tools, folders, or layers before they are needed.

## Project Defaults
- Python 3.11+
- Package and environment manager: `uv`
- Web framework: FastAPI
- Settings: `pydantic-settings`
- LLM provider: OpenAI by default
- Default low-cost model: `gpt-4o-mini`, configurable through `OPENAI_MODEL`

## Definition of Done
- The code runs through documented `uv` commands.
- Relevant tests or manual checks pass.
- No secrets are committed.
- External provider calls are isolated behind a service/client layer.
- Documentation is updated when setup, behavior, or architecture changes.

## Checklist
- [ ] Scope is clear.
- [ ] Existing patterns were reviewed.
- [ ] Environment variables are documented in `.env.example`.
- [ ] No API key or secret is hardcoded.
- [ ] Tests target project logic, not real provider APIs.
- [ ] Second Brain documentation is updated when the session or learning changes.

